<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-08-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="259" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d259">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hart</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-08-21"><hi rend="italic">August 21,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hart inquires if he is to understand, from Department’s instruction
                            No. 407, of June 28, 1902, that due compensation must be made at the
                            time of seizure of property; and states that American citizens must
                            continue to suffer without practical remedy if such rule is not
                            observed.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>